1. Open https://console.developers.google.com/apis/credentials?pli=1
2. Select or create a project
3. Choose "credentials" on the left then create a credential "Oauth Client ID"
4. You may need to first configure "consent screen"
5. Choose "Other" as the application type for the credential being created.
6. Copy out the "client id" and "client secret" then close
7. Run "git clone https://github.com/googleads/googleads-php-lib.git" in your command prompt. You will get a googleads-php-lib directory. Navigate to it by running "cd googleads-php-lib".
8. Run "php composer.phar install". This will install all dependencies needed for running examples.
9. Run "cd examples/Auth/" then run "php GetRefreshToken.php" and follow the prompts
10. Copy out the refresh token
11. Open Adwords Account Manager https://adwords.google.com/um/identity
12. Make sure you have chosen the same email account as for the Auth process initially created, can change from the top right dropdown
13. Fill the form (note that only few currencies are supported for test API)
11. Set up your adsapi_php.ini file with the credential